# Root-level .dockerignore — scopes the Docker build context down when a
# Dockerfile needs `image_build_context` set to the repo root (currently only
# lab-ui/backend/Dockerfile, which also needs the sibling attack-scripts/ dir).
# Keeps the context small; does not affect any other tooling.

.git
.github
.claude
reference
docs/assets
detections
hyperautomation
parsers
cloudflare
tasks

lab-ui/frontend
lab-ui/deploy-test
lab-ui/README.md
lab-ui/docker-compose.yml
lab-ui/docker-compose.override.yml

attack-scripts/logs
attack-scripts/README.md

**/__pycache__
**/node_modules
**/.DS_Store
.wrangler

.env.local
.env.example
.mcp.json

# *.md is broadly excluded (most docs aren't needed in the backend image),
# except the specific files the Docs viewer serves (docs_registry.py) — a
# directory-level exclude can't be selectively un-ignored for nested files,
# which is why `docs` above is scoped to just `docs/assets` rather than the
# whole tree.
*.md
!README.md
!ARCHITECTURE.md
!docs/*.md
